President Cyril Ramaphosa announced his much-anticipated cabinet on Wednesday. Courtesy of #DSTV403 JOHANNESBURG - Trade union federation Cosatu has commented on President Cyril Ramaphosa's announcement of his cabinet on Wednesday. The union's president Zingiswa Losi said they are happy with the selected cabinet and believe that those who have been chosen were selected based on their experience and capabilities. LIVESTREAM: President Ramaphosa announces his cabinet "The fact that the cabinet consists of 50 percent of women, young people and also the experience for the purposes of continuation." "Most importantly for us is the work that needs to happen and we believe that those that have been appointed as ministers and deputy ministers have been appointed on the basis of their capability and experience that they have", said Losi. Cabinet members will be sworn in on Thursday.